{"title":"How to watch the UCI World Championships road races 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-uci-world-championships-road-race","date":1727272501000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-uci-world-championships-road-race\">How to watch the UCI World Championships road races 2024</a></p>\n\n<p>The big one is almost here. The 2024 UCI World Championships road races are this weekend, with riders aiming to win the rainbow jersey on a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uci-road-cycling-world-championships-route-tv-guide-all-you-need-to-know\" target=\"_blank\">hilly route in Zürich, Switzerland</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lotte Kopecky and Mathieu van der Poel will be looking to retain their titles from <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/uci-world-championships-2023-highlights\" target=\"_blank\">Glasgow</a>, but plenty of strong contenders are looking to dethrone them, including potential historic victories should Tadej Pogačar or Remco Evenepoel win <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/uci-world-championships-road-race-mens-favourites\" target=\"_blank\">the men’s race</a> or if Marianne Vos is victorious in <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/uci-world-championships-road-race-womens-favourites\" target=\"_blank\">the women’s race</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are far more races going on this week though, with junior and U23 road races as well as a paracycling categories.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the UK coverage will be free to watch on <a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/mediacentre/articles/2024/uci-cycling-world-championships-how-to-watch\" target=\"_blank\">the BBC</a>, either via the iPlayer or on BBC Two for the elite races. Below are the details on how to watch the action on TV and streaming worldwide.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>UCI World Championships 2024 broadcasters</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Across Africa: </strong>SuperSport</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Across Central and South America and the Caribbean: </strong>ESPN</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Across Europe: </strong>Eurosport/Discovery+</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Albania: </strong>RTSH</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Australia: </strong>SBS, Fox Sports</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Belgium: </strong>RTBF, Sporza</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Brunei: </strong>Astro</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Canada: </strong>Flo Sports</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>China: </strong>CCTV+5</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Czech Republic: </strong>Czech TV</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Denmark: </strong>TV2</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>France: </strong>France TV</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Germany: </strong>ZDF</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Italy: </strong>RAI</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Japan: </strong>J-Sport</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Malaysia: </strong>Astro</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Netherlands: </strong>NOS</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Norway: </strong>TV2</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Philippines: </strong>TAP</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Poland: </strong>TVP</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Singapore: </strong>Starhub</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Slovakia: </strong>RTV SLK</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Slovenia: </strong>RTV SLO</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Spain: </strong>TVE</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Sweden: </strong>SVT</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Switzerland: </strong>SRG/SSR</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Thailand: </strong>JKN, True Vision</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>United Kingdom: </strong>BBC</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>USA: </strong>Flo Sports</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@ucichannel\" target=\"_blank\">UCI’s YouTube</a> and Facebook will also be live streaming the action in some territories.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n            